-- Canadian Employment Insurance Recipients Fell 0.5% in April
-- B y   T h e o p h i l o s   A r g i t i s
-- 2013-06-20T12:30:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-20/canadian-employment-insurance-recipients-fell-0-5-in-april.html
The number of Canadians receiving
jobless benefits fell 0.5 percent in April from the previous
month,  Statistics Canada  said.  The number of regular beneficiaries declined by 2,450 to
521,6300. From the year-ago month, the total number of
beneficiaries fell 4.7 percent, or by 25,990, the Ottawa-based
agency said today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theophilos Argitis in Ottawa at 
